<% content_for :title, "Kickoff notes — Alcovo" %>

<%# The title is editable: click it, or use the standard context menu's Rename. %>
<%# Both live inside this editable controller's scope (no persistence — stub). %>
<div data-controller="editable">
  <%= render "shared/canvas_head", crumbs: [["Message Board", list_view_path], ["Kickoff notes", nil]] do %>
    <button type="button" class="menu__item" role="menuitem" data-action="editable#edit" popovertarget="canvas-menu" popovertargetaction="hide">Rename</button>
    <button type="button" class="menu__item" role="menuitem">Duplicate</button>
    <hr class="menu__separator">
    <button type="button" class="menu__item" role="menuitem">Delete</button>
  <% end %>

  <header class="perma-header">
    <h1 class="perma-header__title editable__display" data-editable-target="display"
        data-action="click->editable#edit" title="Click to rename" tabindex="0">Kickoff notes for the winter issue</h1>
    <input class="perma-header__title editable__input" data-editable-target="input" aria-label="Title" hidden
           data-action="blur->editable#save keydown.enter->editable#save keydown.esc->editable#cancel">
    <p class="perma-header__content u-text-muted">
      <span class="u-text-strong">Ada Lovelace</span> · Jun 27 · <span class="badge badge--accent">Announcement</span>
    </p>
  </header>
</div>

<article class="u-flow">
  <p>We landed on three pieces for the winter issue: the long-form essay, two shorter columns, and the interview. This note tracks the outline and open questions.</p>
  <p>Draft outline is attached. Please leave comments on structure by Friday — especially whether the interview should open or close the issue.</p>
  <p>Once the outline is approved I'll assign sections and set deadlines.</p>
</article>
